The paper deals with the problem of estimating sparsity in various settings, such as group testing and compressed sensing, which are common topics in information theory (cs.IT), data structures (cs.DS), and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of coding theory and probabilistic methods also suggests a possible fit with the sub-categories of signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM).
